article.headline: Hawaii 81, Boise State 67
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Matt Gibson scored 14 of his 21 points in the second half and Bobby Nash scored eight of his 12 points during a key second-half run as Hawaii defeated Boise State 81-67 in a Western Athletic Conference game Wednesday night. With both teams trading baskets for most of the second half, Nash scored eight points during an 11-2 run with less than five minutes remaining in the game. The Rainbow Warriors (14-7, 6-7 WAC), who led by no more than six points in the second half, took a 72-62 lead on Nash's basket with two minutes remaining. The Broncos, meanwhile, struggled from the field, making just one field goal in the game's final four minutes. Coby Karl led Boise State (10-15, 4-10 WAC) with 19 points, while Jermaine Blackburn added 16. Vaidotas Peciukas scored 15 points off the bench for Hawaii, and teammate Jake Sottos added 11.
